This is a placeholder file. To create an actual Excel example, create a file with following structure:

Column A: Camera Name (optional - will create ALL cameras for each branch)
Column B: IP Address (optional - used for both branch and camera)  
Column C: Branch Name (required)
Column D: Phone Number (optional)

Example data showing MULTIPLE cameras per branch:
| A         | B             | C     | D           |
|-----------|---------------|-------|-------------|
| كاميرا مدخل | 192.168.1.1   | فرع 1 | 01234567890 |
| كاميرا خزينة | 192.168.1.2   | فرع 1 | 01234567890 |
| كاميرا خارجية | 192.168.1.3   | فرع 1 | 01234567890 |
| كاميرا رئيسية | 192.168.2.1   | فرع 2 | 01123456789 |
| كاميرا فرعية | 192.168.2.2   | فرع 2 | 01123456789 |
| كاميرا مخزن | 192.168.3.1   | فرع 3 | 01098765432 |
| كاميرا موقف | 192.168.3.2   | فرع 3 | 01098765432 |

NEW FEATURES:
- Multiple cameras per branch support
- All cameras with same branch name will be grouped together
- Creates branch once with ALL its cameras
- Updates existing branches and adds missing cameras
- Prevents duplicate cameras by name within same branch

RESULT:
- فرع 1: 3 cameras
- فرع 2: 2 cameras  
- فرع 3: 2 cameras

Total: 3 branches + 7 cameras
